In reply to the second point, regarding less prejudice, we say that it is a vicious statement in the present question because not even trifling prejudicc is caused by the victor, or if there was any, still what the statutes and common law give him should not be taken from him for the simple reason that it harms the other party or causes him greater prejudice. ὓ He does not cause an injury who is exercis- ing his own rights.
